1
00:00:38,976 --> 00:00:42,521
No matter how I think about it,
there's only one way.

2
00:00:42,605 --> 00:00:43,939
NO MORE GAMBLING!

3
00:00:44,023 --> 00:00:45,483
The prosecutor.

4
00:00:46,651 --> 00:00:49,153
- Let's take her out.
- But, boss.

5
00:00:49,236 --> 00:00:52,698
Going after a prosecutor
will make things worse.

6
00:00:52,782 --> 00:00:56,369
- Damn, I knew he'd be trouble.
- Get your best men ready.

7
00:00:56,494 --> 00:00:59,121
So they can do the job
when the time is right.

8
00:01:05,878 --> 00:01:07,505
HILLSIDE CAFE

9
00:01:13,969 --> 00:01:16,180
Yes, she's arrived.

10
00:01:16,263 --> 00:01:18,182
She just went into the Hillside Cafe.

11
00:01:18,265 --> 00:01:20,267
Hillside Cafe?

12
00:01:27,274 --> 00:01:28,734
Come on, pick up.

13
00:01:59,056 --> 00:02:01,517
This is driving me crazy.

14
00:02:14,613 --> 00:02:15,948
Taxi!

15
00:02:16,991 --> 00:02:18,159
Wait!

16
00:02:27,501 --> 00:02:30,421
The Passenger Ship Spy Case,
the Kwon Soon-bok Case

17
00:02:30,504 --> 00:02:33,632
and the suicide in March.

18
00:02:33,716 --> 00:02:37,428
Han Gyeong-wook and Yoo In-gu
are definitely linked to these.

19
00:02:37,511 --> 00:02:40,723
That ship that sank ten years ago.

20
00:02:40,806 --> 00:02:42,391
I was on that ship.

21
00:02:42,892 --> 00:02:47,062
And I know everything about the incident
you're so curious about.

22
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:51,442
Could Gang Beom-ryong
be the one to solve this puzzle?

23
00:03:14,799 --> 00:03:15,925
Get him out of here.

24
00:03:28,521 --> 00:03:30,022
Prosecutor Gang.

25
00:03:30,105 --> 00:03:31,899
About what you asked last time.

26
00:03:31,982 --> 00:03:34,068
I think I have an answer for you.

27
00:03:34,151 --> 00:03:35,319
Is now a good time?

28
00:03:35,402 --> 00:03:36,946
Oh.

29
00:03:37,947 --> 00:03:39,240
I see.

30
00:03:39,949 --> 00:03:41,367
Yes, have a seat.

31
00:03:42,284 --> 00:03:45,162
Actually, it's a bit too loud in here.

32
00:03:45,246 --> 00:03:46,622
Come with me.

33
00:03:52,628 --> 00:03:53,629
Huh?

34
00:04:16,026 --> 00:04:17,862
Hey, grab her!

35
00:04:22,616 --> 00:04:25,411
Hey, open the door! Open up!

36
00:04:41,218 --> 00:04:43,804
How could you let her get away?

37
00:04:43,888 --> 00:04:47,016
- Why are you calling on a regular phone?
- Hey, Ho-myeong.

38
00:04:47,099 --> 00:04:49,059
It's an emergency.
Get over here right now.

39
00:04:49,143 --> 00:04:50,978
What are you talking about? I can't.

40
00:04:51,061 --> 00:04:54,273
- I'm at a show.
- It's Yoo In-gu's crew.

41
00:04:54,356 --> 00:04:57,985
- They're coming to take out Gang.
- What?

42
00:04:58,068 --> 00:04:59,987
- Where are you?
- I'm on Yeongseon Island.

43
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:03,365
- Prosecutor Gang is on Yeongseon Island?
- Yeah.

44
00:05:03,449 --> 00:05:04,825
Prosecutor Gang

45
00:05:05,492 --> 00:05:08,621
provoked Yoo In-gu,
and now that crazy son of a bitch...

46
00:05:08,704 --> 00:05:11,540
Look, there's no time to explain.
Just get over here, fast!

47
00:05:12,958 --> 00:05:14,293
You must be kidding me.

48
00:05:14,376 --> 00:05:16,837
If you just stay put,
Prosecutor Gang will die, you idiot.

49
00:05:19,423 --> 00:05:22,384
If we lose her now, it's all over.

50
00:05:38,692 --> 00:05:40,444
Damn it.

51
00:05:48,077 --> 00:05:49,578
Ram her!

52
00:05:51,872 --> 00:05:53,499
- I can't.
- Just do it!

53
00:05:53,582 --> 00:05:54,583
Just one more...

54
00:05:56,752 --> 00:05:57,920
Just hit her!

55
00:06:00,881 --> 00:06:03,550
What are you doing, you idiot?
Step on it already!

56
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:19,483
Why won't it stop?

57
00:06:26,198 --> 00:06:28,409
Where do these bastards
think they're going?

58
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:39,837
- Why can't you get past her?
- Damn it.

59
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,046
Shit.

60
00:06:59,314 --> 00:07:00,315
Ram her!

61
00:07:04,528 --> 00:07:08,198
Harder!

62
00:08:06,924 --> 00:08:08,926
Hey! What the hell?

63
00:08:28,570 --> 00:08:30,781
YOU CAN LEAVE DEAD, NEVER ALIVE!

64
00:08:35,285 --> 00:08:37,162
Thank you.

65
00:08:46,797 --> 00:08:50,134
LOSE LAND, LOSE HOME, END UP IN DEBT.
YOU CAN LEAVE DEAD, NEVER ALIVE!

66
00:09:20,539 --> 00:09:21,540
Jesus Christ!

67
00:09:23,876 --> 00:09:25,127
It's a ghost.

68
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:28,046
Hey, wait.

69
00:09:28,172 --> 00:09:30,799
I think I saw a ghost.
The ghost of a young woman.

70
00:09:30,883 --> 00:09:32,634
You get scared so easily.

71
00:09:33,927 --> 00:09:36,722
What kind of job could be
in a place like this?

72
00:09:37,723 --> 00:09:41,310
Look. She's taking us there to be sold.

73
00:09:41,393 --> 00:09:42,519
I can hear you, you know?

74
00:09:43,478 --> 00:09:46,356
This place used to be packed with people.

75
00:09:46,857 --> 00:09:49,943
- But everyone got chased out.
- But why?

76
00:09:51,403 --> 00:09:52,613
Hey, we're here.

77
00:09:54,823 --> 00:09:57,367
- Just get over here.
- Unbelievable.

78
00:10:02,289 --> 00:10:06,960
They barged in and trashed the place
just to catch one woman.

79
00:10:09,171 --> 00:10:11,006
Where did those people go?

80
00:10:11,089 --> 00:10:13,717
I don't know.
They just sped off in their car.

81
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:16,678
- Which way did they go?
- That way, toward the main road.

82
00:10:32,486 --> 00:10:34,446
Why is Jeong Ho-myeong here?

83
00:10:34,529 --> 00:10:35,530
Gang Beom-ryong.

84
00:10:35,614 --> 00:10:38,367
Why did he show up?
And at a time like this?

85
00:10:38,450 --> 00:10:40,786
Looked like he was looking for
some thugs and a woman.

86
00:10:40,869 --> 00:10:42,829
Is it Prosecutor Gang?

87
00:10:42,913 --> 00:10:45,082
I wonder if Ma Gong-bok
had a different idea.

88
00:10:45,165 --> 00:10:48,168
That means he came to meet
Prosecutor Gang too.

89
00:10:48,252 --> 00:10:51,713
This isn't the time
to worry about Gang Beom-ryong.

90
00:10:51,797 --> 00:10:53,382
My priority is Gang.

91
00:10:53,465 --> 00:10:55,634
Anyway, there's no way that guy knows me.

92
00:10:55,717 --> 00:10:57,261
- For now...
- For now...

93
00:10:57,344 --> 00:10:59,096
- Play it cool.
- Play it cool.

94
00:11:25,706 --> 00:11:26,999
Why the hell are you here?

95
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:30,961
- This isn't a coincidence, is it?
- You.

96
00:11:31,044 --> 00:11:32,296
Do you know who I am?

97
00:11:32,671 --> 00:11:35,632
- What the hell is this?
- Tell me. How did you know?

98
00:11:37,676 --> 00:11:40,387
Are you just playing dumb,
or are you really that clueless?

99
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:44,099
Anyway, I don't have time to fool around.
Get out of the way.

100
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,978
You were looking for
Prosecutor Gang, right?

101
00:11:48,061 --> 00:11:50,522
Hurry up and tell me what's going on.

102
00:11:54,443 --> 00:11:57,446
She's in danger right now.

103
00:12:15,422 --> 00:12:16,423
What the hell?

104
00:12:17,841 --> 00:12:19,176
You're tailing her, aren't you?

105
00:12:20,052 --> 00:12:22,346
I need to see her too. Let's go together.

106
00:12:22,429 --> 00:12:23,430
What?

107
00:12:23,513 --> 00:12:25,557
Are you crazy? Get out.

108
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,559
Hey, you think I want to be doing this?

109
00:12:27,642 --> 00:12:29,686
If I'd brought my own car...

110
00:12:29,770 --> 00:12:32,189
- Think this is a taxi?
- I'll pay you well.

111
00:12:32,272 --> 00:12:34,691
You don't even know where she went.

112
00:12:35,942 --> 00:12:38,070
Are you saying you know?

113
00:12:38,195 --> 00:12:39,237
Hold on.

114
00:12:40,781 --> 00:12:43,158
Seriously, where did she go?

115
00:12:51,249 --> 00:12:53,210
- Yes, boss.
- Hey, Gong-bok.

116
00:12:53,293 --> 00:12:54,836
Can you pull some CCTV footage now?

117
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:55,962
Right now?

118
00:12:56,046 --> 00:12:59,466
Hold on, the CCTV footage from where?

119
00:12:59,549 --> 00:13:02,844
The Hillside Cafe in Nakwon-ri.
Pull the footage from 30 minutes ago.

120
00:13:02,928 --> 00:13:04,846
Look for suspicious vehicles leaving.

121
00:13:04,930 --> 00:13:08,100
- Vehicles?
- Trace their route and contact me. Hurry.

122
00:13:08,183 --> 00:13:10,977
- What's going on?
- No time to explain.

123
00:13:11,061 --> 00:13:13,397
- Just text it to me.
- But...

124
00:13:15,232 --> 00:13:17,651
I'm so damn busy as is.

125
00:13:19,111 --> 00:13:20,445
YEONGSEON ISLAND, NAKWON-RO

126
00:13:24,908 --> 00:13:30,163
HANMAEUM SOCIAL DANCE

127
00:13:34,292 --> 00:13:35,585
Come in.

128
00:13:37,504 --> 00:13:38,839
Aren't you coming in?

129
00:13:42,259 --> 00:13:44,136
Come on, get in.

130
00:13:54,104 --> 00:13:55,397
Just a moment.

131
00:14:09,661 --> 00:14:10,745
Come on up.

132
00:14:16,543 --> 00:14:21,214
This first floor used to be a supermarket,
and the second was cheap single rooms.

133
00:14:35,687 --> 00:14:37,147
Why is he staring?

134
00:14:45,071 --> 00:14:46,239
Hey, there.

135
00:14:46,823 --> 00:14:47,824
Jesus.

136
00:15:07,052 --> 00:15:08,053
Hey.

137
00:15:08,970 --> 00:15:11,264
This is either a pyramid scheme or a cult.

138
00:15:11,348 --> 00:15:14,851
- Let's get out of here.
- Hey, come on. Lee would never.

139
00:15:14,935 --> 00:15:16,102
Aren't you coming up?

140
00:15:17,979 --> 00:15:20,857
Hey. Can you just tell us now?

141
00:15:21,650 --> 00:15:24,152
What exactly is this place?

142
00:15:25,153 --> 00:15:27,405
You can think of it as
a temporary shelter.

143
00:15:27,489 --> 00:15:28,740
A temporary shelter?

144
00:15:28,823 --> 00:15:32,452
Everyone in there
is in the same boat as you are.

145
00:15:32,536 --> 00:15:36,998
They lost their homes to Heaven Capital
and were thrown onto the street overnight.

146
00:15:37,082 --> 00:15:40,126
Our Dance Club set this place up
to help people like them.

147
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:44,297
- It's just temporary.
- Wait, a place like this...

148
00:15:44,381 --> 00:15:46,508
...was set up by a Dance Club?

149
00:15:46,591 --> 00:15:50,178
We used to have a few members
in our Dance Club

150
00:15:50,262 --> 00:15:51,763
who had family problems.

151
00:15:53,265 --> 00:15:55,058
- Come on up.
- Okay.

152
00:16:06,945 --> 00:16:08,905
SEVERAL VEHICLES GOT INTO A CAR CHASE
AND HEADED TOWARDS YEONGSEON RIVER

153
00:16:08,989 --> 00:16:10,073
Make your choice.

154
00:16:13,368 --> 00:16:16,621
Trying to take credit
for what Ma Gong-bok sent?

155
00:16:17,747 --> 00:16:18,748
You know Gong-bok, too?

156
00:16:18,832 --> 00:16:21,251
You think I wouldn't notice
pathetic thugs like you?

157
00:16:21,334 --> 00:16:24,921
- Are you sure he checked properly?
- You don't have time to be doubting me.

158
00:16:25,005 --> 00:16:27,007
You said Prosecutor Gang's in danger.

159
00:16:30,552 --> 00:16:32,554
HILLSIDE CAFE

160
00:16:56,244 --> 00:17:00,040
My family's threatening to disown me
for losing our family burial ground.

161
00:17:00,123 --> 00:17:02,792
- What am I to do?
- Well, why did you sign off on it?

162
00:17:02,917 --> 00:17:04,294
You try dealing with them!

163
00:17:04,586 --> 00:17:06,713
Could you stand up to them
when they threaten you?

164
00:17:06,796 --> 00:17:07,797
Shut it!

165
00:17:08,673 --> 00:17:11,635
Back in my day,
I didn't even blink if I got stabbed.

166
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,303
How dare you?

167
00:17:14,387 --> 00:17:16,890
- Mr. Park, we're here.
- Yeah.

168
00:17:16,973 --> 00:17:21,061
Anyway, you have to keep your promise
about getting the family burial ground.

169
00:17:26,483 --> 00:17:29,986
Where is everyone?
Why do I always get stuck with this?

170
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:33,948
The others all had plans, you know.
And you're the best at this.

171
00:17:34,074 --> 00:17:36,910
They start all this,
then leave me to clean up the mess...

172
00:17:39,579 --> 00:17:40,580
And who are they?

173
00:17:41,122 --> 00:17:42,749
Why'd you bring these stragglers?

174
00:17:42,832 --> 00:17:45,502
I told you about him.
Manager Bong from my company.

175
00:17:46,169 --> 00:17:47,170
Say hello.

176
00:17:47,253 --> 00:17:49,964
This is Mr. Park Chun-sik.
He's in charge of this shelter.

177
00:17:50,048 --> 00:17:51,341
Ah, the boss.

178
00:17:51,424 --> 00:17:54,177
Pleasure to meet you.
My name is Bong Je-sun.

179
00:17:54,260 --> 00:17:56,137
Ah.

180
00:17:56,262 --> 00:18:00,517
The poor guy who lost his house and job
because of his nephew?

181
00:18:02,894 --> 00:18:04,688
Did they tell you what this place is?

182
00:18:05,105 --> 00:18:09,150
- And what you have to do?
- I was told it's a temporary shelter.

183
00:18:10,568 --> 00:18:12,904
That's a nice way of putting it.

184
00:18:12,987 --> 00:18:17,575
We feed and house people
who lost their homes to those thugs.

185
00:18:17,659 --> 00:18:20,870
You won't find a charity case
bigger than this.

186
00:18:21,287 --> 00:18:23,498
And not a single cent from the government.

187
00:18:23,581 --> 00:18:27,210
I'm working myself to the bone
trying to run this place.

188
00:18:27,293 --> 00:18:29,546
And my joints are killing me.

189
00:18:29,629 --> 00:18:31,047
Well, you're doing a good thing.

190
00:18:31,548 --> 00:18:32,966
Right, a good thing.

191
00:18:33,049 --> 00:18:36,344
But do you think I should be
doing it all by myself?

192
00:18:37,303 --> 00:18:39,013
So while you're staying here,

193
00:18:39,139 --> 00:18:42,559
you can help with cleaning, maintenance,
and a little cooking.

194
00:18:43,351 --> 00:18:47,188
- So, it's a kind of...
- You're asking him to be a slave.

195
00:18:48,022 --> 00:18:49,441
What? A slave?

196
00:18:50,066 --> 00:18:51,568
Don't be ridiculous.

197
00:18:51,693 --> 00:18:54,362
We provide room and board.
We'll even pay you a little.

198
00:18:54,446 --> 00:18:57,574
And we're trying to get people's
illegally seized homes back.

199
00:18:57,657 --> 00:18:59,701
Where else will you find
a perfect job like this?

200
00:18:59,784 --> 00:19:01,244
Can we get our homes back?

201
00:19:01,327 --> 00:19:03,830
Well, the number of victims
keeps increasing,

202
00:19:04,205 --> 00:19:07,000
so we're trying to come up with
a plan ourselves.

203
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:09,919
Hey, you're not actually buying this,
are you?

204
00:19:10,003 --> 00:19:13,506
They're just trying to use you!

205
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:17,594
- Seriously!
- Hey, who's this little punk?

206
00:19:17,677 --> 00:19:18,970
Hey, old man.

207
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:23,349
I get that my uncle looks
like an easy target.

208
00:19:23,433 --> 00:19:25,393
You probably think you can
take advantage of him.

209
00:19:25,477 --> 00:19:29,063
He may be, but I'm no pushover. Got it?

210
00:19:30,482 --> 00:19:31,649
Let's go.

211
00:19:31,775 --> 00:19:33,443
Go where?

212
00:19:33,526 --> 00:19:35,653
You want to stay in a dump like this?

213
00:19:35,779 --> 00:19:38,740
- Have some pride.
- What? A dump?

214
00:19:39,324 --> 00:19:43,328
- A dump? This little punk...
- Stop it. What are you doing?

215
00:19:43,453 --> 00:19:45,830
Okay. All right.

216
00:19:45,914 --> 00:19:49,250
We don't need a punk like you.

217
00:19:49,334 --> 00:19:50,877
As far as I can tell?

218
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:54,005
You're a lost cause.
You couldn't do the job right anyway.

219
00:19:54,088 --> 00:19:55,673
"Punk?"

220
00:19:59,803 --> 00:20:01,054
Old man.

221
00:20:02,055 --> 00:20:03,056
Do you know me?

222
00:20:03,139 --> 00:20:05,892
Hey, Heo Nam-il.
Why are you being so rude?

223
00:20:05,975 --> 00:20:09,145
Uncle, didn't you hear
that old man insulting me?

224
00:20:09,229 --> 00:20:11,773
You're being insulting.
You called this place a dump.

225
00:20:12,524 --> 00:20:13,608
Apologize right now.

226
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,569
Why should I apologize?

227
00:20:18,780 --> 00:20:21,241
You think that's right?
What about this one?

228
00:20:22,492 --> 00:20:26,371
I'm not going to live like a slave
in a dump like this.

229
00:20:26,496 --> 00:20:27,539
You can stay.

230
00:20:30,291 --> 00:20:32,418
Calm down.

231
00:20:32,502 --> 00:20:34,087
I'm so sorry.

232
00:20:35,088 --> 00:20:36,214
I'm sorry.

233
00:20:37,215 --> 00:20:38,633
He's not normally like that.

234
00:20:38,716 --> 00:20:40,552
I don't know what's gotten into him.
I'll go get him.

235
00:20:40,635 --> 00:20:41,678
Man, that hurts.

236
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:43,263
Hey, Heo Nam-il!

237
00:20:44,848 --> 00:20:46,140
Unbelievable.

238
00:20:47,141 --> 00:20:50,228
They don't look alike at all.
Is he really his uncle?

239
00:20:52,689 --> 00:20:54,315
SEVERAL VEHICLES GOT INTO A CAR CHASE
AND HEADED TOWARDS YEONGSEON RIVER

240
00:20:57,193 --> 00:20:59,279
Earlier, at the cafe.

241
00:20:59,362 --> 00:21:02,115
Those thugs work for Yoo In-gu, right?

242
00:21:02,198 --> 00:21:05,535
Why is that bastard Yoo In-gu after Gang?

243
00:21:05,618 --> 00:21:06,703
You know why, don't you?

244
00:21:06,786 --> 00:21:09,747
Even if I knew,
you think I'd tell a punk like you?

245
00:21:09,831 --> 00:21:11,040
A punk like me?

246
00:21:11,124 --> 00:21:15,044
The enemy who ruined my operation.
The stalker on my tail for a decade.

247
00:21:15,128 --> 00:21:18,298
A Hwasan Sect gangster pretending
to be a convenience store owner.

248
00:21:18,381 --> 00:21:19,382
You...

249
00:21:19,465 --> 00:21:22,093
- You knew all along.
- Stop acting like my buddy.

250
00:21:22,176 --> 00:21:24,721
I could easily toss you off this car.

251
00:21:25,346 --> 00:21:26,723
What did you say?

252
00:21:37,567 --> 00:21:38,568
What happened here?

253
00:21:39,235 --> 00:21:40,904
A car fell into the river.

254
00:21:45,283 --> 00:21:47,702
Could it be Gang?

255
00:21:49,621 --> 00:21:50,747
Hold on.

256
00:21:52,373 --> 00:21:53,374
That bastard.

257
00:21:56,377 --> 00:21:58,254
He's one of Yoo In-gu's men.

258
00:22:01,049 --> 00:22:03,259
What's he doing here now?

259
00:22:07,096 --> 00:22:09,265
Could they have already gotten her?

260
00:22:10,475 --> 00:22:11,559
Hey! Wait!

261
00:22:11,643 --> 00:22:13,436
Hey! Where are you going?

262
00:22:13,519 --> 00:22:15,647
Hey, stop! I'm coming with you!

263
00:22:21,611 --> 00:22:22,904
Nam-il.

264
00:22:24,739 --> 00:22:26,199
- Nam-il!
- What?

265
00:22:28,534 --> 00:22:30,286
You can't just leave like this.

266
00:22:30,954 --> 00:22:33,539
- Let's go back. I'll talk to them.
- Go by yourself.

267
00:22:34,082 --> 00:22:35,458
I'm going to a friend's.

268
00:22:36,459 --> 00:22:37,961
Don't you know thugs are chasing us?

269
00:22:38,044 --> 00:22:41,506
Yeah, and why would that be?
They've already taken our house.

270
00:22:42,131 --> 00:22:46,094
It's because you beat their guys up.

271
00:22:46,177 --> 00:22:47,762
I can't believe what I'm hearing.

272
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,640
Whose fault is it that we're in this mess?

273
00:22:50,723 --> 00:22:51,766
This is my fault?

274
00:22:51,849 --> 00:22:52,850
Who else?

275
00:22:52,934 --> 00:22:56,062
You're always getting into trouble.
You've been held back two years!

276
00:22:56,145 --> 00:22:58,398
And you even lost the house.
When are you going to grow up?

277
00:22:58,481 --> 00:23:00,233
Then pretend I don't exist!

278
00:23:01,943 --> 00:23:03,945
After all, we're not even related.

279
00:23:07,573 --> 00:23:09,033
Nam-il! Seriously.

280
00:23:09,117 --> 00:23:10,660
Hey.

281
00:23:12,662 --> 00:23:15,456
- Are you really leaving?
- Think I enjoy calling you Uncle?

282
00:23:16,332 --> 00:23:19,168
I felt sorry you had no memory
and nowhere to go.

283
00:23:20,169 --> 00:23:22,046
So I was playing family with you.

284
00:23:24,048 --> 00:23:25,049
And Grandpa's house?

285
00:23:26,050 --> 00:23:28,302
It's not your house, but mine.

286
00:23:29,220 --> 00:23:32,181
So stop meddling
and promising you'll get it back.

287
00:23:33,182 --> 00:23:35,059
From now on,
let's just go our separate ways.

288
00:23:35,685 --> 00:23:36,853
Okay?

289
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:09,677
- Hey, did you find him?
- We were one step behind.

290
00:24:09,761 --> 00:24:12,472
Prosecutor Gang's car crashed
into the Yeongseon River.

291
00:24:12,597 --> 00:24:14,891
It looks like she was
being chased by Yoo In-gu.

292
00:24:15,016 --> 00:24:16,017
You're saying she's dead?

293
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,977
Don't know yet.
They're recovering the vehicle.

294
00:24:18,061 --> 00:24:19,520
Where are you? Let's meet.

295
00:24:19,604 --> 00:24:20,605
No, no.

296
00:24:21,564 --> 00:24:23,316
No, Ho-myeong. Then you should just...

297
00:24:23,399 --> 00:24:25,193
You should just go back.

298
00:24:25,735 --> 00:24:27,070
What are you saying?

299
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:31,282
Didn't you say you were with your family?

300
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,534
Go back to them now.

301
00:24:33,618 --> 00:24:36,704
I can't go back now.
I have to see if Gang is alive.

302
00:24:36,829 --> 00:24:41,250
They're just pulling up the car now.
It'll take all day to know.

303
00:24:41,334 --> 00:24:44,754
I'll tap into the police radio,
so you hurry back.

304
00:24:44,837 --> 00:24:47,548
The show's already over. It's too late.

305
00:24:47,632 --> 00:24:48,633
Hey, man.

306
00:24:48,716 --> 00:24:51,969
The longer you drag out a fight,
the worse it's going to be.

307
00:24:52,053 --> 00:24:56,224
We haven't even found Gang.
You want to lose your wife too?

308
00:24:59,519 --> 00:25:00,603
All right.

309
00:25:00,686 --> 00:25:02,772
- Call me if anything happens.
- Got it.

310
00:25:45,314 --> 00:25:48,317
- Grandpa. There's someone over there.
- Where?

311
00:25:48,401 --> 00:25:50,403
- Over there!
- Oh, dear.

312
00:25:50,486 --> 00:25:51,779
Go on, hurry!

313
00:25:52,780 --> 00:25:54,157
What on earth?

314
00:25:58,953 --> 00:26:00,496
Miss, wake up.

315
00:26:00,580 --> 00:26:02,039
Can you hear me?

316
00:26:03,499 --> 00:26:05,918
Grandpa, that's not a woman.

317
00:26:06,002 --> 00:26:07,879
He's a man. Look!

318
00:26:45,875 --> 00:26:46,959
Je-sun?

319
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:05,853
I...

320
00:27:08,314 --> 00:27:09,523
don't remember.

321
00:27:09,649 --> 00:27:11,734
You really don't remember anything?

322
00:27:12,985 --> 00:27:16,322
Your age, your name, your parents.

323
00:27:17,907 --> 00:27:18,908
Nothing?

324
00:27:19,408 --> 00:27:21,911
No. I don't know.

325
00:27:30,795 --> 00:27:34,966
- You don't have a mom and dad either?
- I don't know.

326
00:27:36,092 --> 00:27:39,220
- I don't know if I do.
- If you really don't...

327
00:27:40,221 --> 00:27:43,057
- do you want to be part of our family?
- Family?

328
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:46,143
I don't just let anyone in,
but I'll make an exception for you.

329
00:27:47,270 --> 00:27:48,938
You can't be my grandpa or dad.

330
00:27:49,772 --> 00:27:51,148
What about my uncle?

331
00:27:51,232 --> 00:27:52,275
Uncle?

332
00:27:53,609 --> 00:27:54,902
An uncle.

333
00:27:56,696 --> 00:28:00,283
- What would an uncle do?
- You have to play with me.

334
00:28:00,366 --> 00:28:01,617
All the time.

335
00:28:03,995 --> 00:28:05,788
You're my uncle now, okay?

336
00:28:07,581 --> 00:28:08,958
Uncle, play with me.

337
00:28:10,835 --> 00:28:14,297
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
BONG JE-SUN, 215 DOYANG-RO, CHUNCHEON

338
00:28:24,682 --> 00:28:26,225
Uncle, are you bored?

339
00:28:27,435 --> 00:28:29,520
If you're so bored,
you can help me with this.

340
00:28:39,447 --> 00:28:41,115
Don't let go.

341
00:28:41,198 --> 00:28:44,118
- First time on a two-wheeler?
- Yeah.

342
00:28:46,412 --> 00:28:47,538
I won't let go.

343
00:29:03,054 --> 00:29:04,305
Where are you right now?

344
00:29:09,393 --> 00:29:10,478
Huh?

345
00:29:21,489 --> 00:29:22,907
Hey!

346
00:29:23,616 --> 00:29:25,826
Hey!

347
00:29:25,910 --> 00:29:27,703
Are you okay? Hey!

348
00:29:28,329 --> 00:29:29,580
Oh, no.

349
00:29:29,663 --> 00:29:31,582
Are you okay? Hey!

350
00:29:32,333 --> 00:29:34,001
Hey!

351
00:29:47,098 --> 00:29:48,265
Can you hear me?

352
00:29:48,349 --> 00:29:50,726
You're okay now. You're alive.

353
00:29:50,810 --> 00:29:56,524
- I'll call 911 for you.
- Don't call anyone.

354
00:29:58,859 --> 00:30:00,986
Hey!

355
00:30:02,405 --> 00:30:03,739
Oh, gosh.

356
00:30:13,082 --> 00:30:14,542
Jeez.

357
00:30:14,667 --> 00:30:17,878
Don't go out of your way to get yelled at.
Give up on him.

358
00:30:18,003 --> 00:30:20,423
With a nephew like that,
would he be any different?

359
00:30:20,548 --> 00:30:24,593
I'm telling you, he's not like that.
He's not picking up.

360
00:30:29,974 --> 00:30:31,016
Mi-kyung.

361
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,269
Didn't you say you had a date today?

362
00:30:33,352 --> 00:30:36,230
I don't know. Don't ask.

363
00:30:36,313 --> 00:30:37,857
Looks to me like you got rejected.

364
00:30:38,649 --> 00:30:40,860
I thought the guy was totally into you.

365
00:30:42,027 --> 00:30:43,279
I don't know, okay?

366
00:30:43,362 --> 00:30:47,158
I may have been rejected in person,
but I've never been ghosted.

367
00:30:47,241 --> 00:30:48,576
I wouldn't be so sure.

368
00:30:52,204 --> 00:30:53,539
Damn it.

369
00:30:53,622 --> 00:30:55,124
O-ran.

370
00:30:55,207 --> 00:30:57,126
Weren't you seeing a show
with your family?

371
00:30:57,209 --> 00:31:01,255
We already saw the show.
I was just dropping Ji-woo off at home.

372
00:31:01,338 --> 00:31:04,091
Already?
Weren't you going somewhere nice after?

373
00:31:04,175 --> 00:31:05,551
Don't ask.

374
00:31:07,428 --> 00:31:09,805
Jeez, things are pretty tense
over here too.

375
00:31:10,473 --> 00:31:13,642
Oh, by the way, Ye-ji,
did the person you were bringing show up?

376
00:31:13,726 --> 00:31:15,144
Is he going to work here?

377
00:31:16,145 --> 00:31:17,313
About that.

378
00:31:17,396 --> 00:31:20,149
He's not answering his phone right now.

379
00:31:32,536 --> 00:31:35,289
She looks pretty hurt.

380
00:31:35,372 --> 00:31:37,082
Shouldn't we take her to a hospital?

381
00:31:37,166 --> 00:31:39,752
Oh, no. No hospital.

382
00:31:39,835 --> 00:31:44,340
No police, no 911.
She kept saying that the whole way here.

383
00:31:46,342 --> 00:31:47,801
I've got a bad feeling about this.

384
00:31:48,344 --> 00:31:51,055
Usually, only people trying
to evade the law

385
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:53,349
go around saying you can't call the cops.

386
00:31:53,432 --> 00:31:56,227
Oh, my! So she's a criminal?

387
00:31:56,852 --> 00:31:57,853
No.

388
00:31:58,521 --> 00:32:00,064
- I think she's a prosecutor.
- What?

389
00:32:02,983 --> 00:32:04,109
- She's a prosecutor.
- Oh, my!

390
00:32:04,902 --> 00:32:07,029
She said not to call anyone.

391
00:32:07,112 --> 00:32:08,948
This wasn't a simple accident.

392
00:32:11,283 --> 00:32:15,496
In that case,
let's just wait until she wakes up.

393
00:32:15,579 --> 00:32:18,624
If she's weird when she wakes up,
Mi-kyung can take care of her.

394
00:32:18,707 --> 00:32:20,668
Yeah, let's do that.

395
00:32:22,670 --> 00:32:23,671
Hey.

396
00:32:25,005 --> 00:32:27,466
- Bong Je-sun, right?
- Yes.

397
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:28,926
I see you left your nephew.

398
00:32:29,009 --> 00:32:31,303
I guess you decided to work
in this dump, huh?

399
00:32:31,387 --> 00:32:33,472
Well, it's not like I abandoned him.

400
00:32:33,556 --> 00:32:35,391
As for the job...

401
00:32:35,474 --> 00:32:37,768
- I'd like to give it a shot.
- All right.

402
00:32:37,851 --> 00:32:39,353
Let's start right away.

403
00:32:39,436 --> 00:32:40,980
Don't think about getting any sleep.

404
00:32:41,063 --> 00:32:44,441
You'll stay here and keep an eye on her.

405
00:32:44,525 --> 00:32:47,570
When she wakes up,
you contact us all immediately.

406
00:32:47,653 --> 00:32:48,654
Got it?

407
00:32:49,321 --> 00:32:50,531
Uh, by myself?

408
00:32:50,614 --> 00:32:51,782
Of course!

409
00:32:51,865 --> 00:32:53,576
You brought her,
so you're responsible for her.

410
00:32:53,659 --> 00:32:55,703
She better not end up a corpse
in my building.

411
00:32:56,245 --> 00:32:57,663
Is that clear?

412
00:33:02,376 --> 00:33:04,420
Grandpa surrenders!
Please just spare my life!

413
00:33:04,503 --> 00:33:05,921
Oh, no!

414
00:33:07,172 --> 00:33:08,340
Hey, it's Daddy.

415
00:33:09,550 --> 00:33:10,843
- Daddy!
- Ji-woo!

416
00:33:10,926 --> 00:33:13,887
I'm sorry I came so late!

417
00:33:13,971 --> 00:33:15,222
- It's okay.
- Did you like the show?

418
00:33:15,306 --> 00:33:16,682
- Yes.
- Hey.

419
00:33:16,765 --> 00:33:19,184
- Just getting home?
- Yes.

420
00:33:19,268 --> 00:33:21,520
Daddy, check out my new mask.

421
00:33:21,604 --> 00:33:24,481
- Isn't it cool?
- Wow, it's so cool.

422
00:33:27,192 --> 00:33:28,360
- Daddy.
- Yeah?

423
00:33:28,444 --> 00:33:30,321
Did you beat the bad guys?

424
00:33:31,655 --> 00:33:32,781
Yes.

425
00:33:34,199 --> 00:33:38,037
- But where's Mom?
- She dropped off Ji-woo and went out.

426
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:41,874
- Where to?
- I don't know. She was furious.

427
00:33:41,957 --> 00:33:45,461
She said she needed to
blow off some steam.

428
00:33:47,463 --> 00:33:50,257
It's okay. Mom will understand.

429
00:34:25,709 --> 00:34:28,587
I'm sorry. I have no excuse, really.

430
00:34:30,506 --> 00:34:31,715
No, I'm sure you do.

431
00:34:32,424 --> 00:34:33,884
Go on.

432
00:34:33,967 --> 00:34:36,428
I'll decide if I'll forgive you
after I hear it.

433
00:34:46,730 --> 00:34:50,275
One of my army buddies
is a guy named Tae-sik.

434
00:34:51,026 --> 00:34:54,363
He came to visit Yeongseon Island
and got into a car accident.

435
00:34:54,446 --> 00:34:58,367
He was panicking and thinking
if he knew anyone on Yeongseon Island.

436
00:34:58,450 --> 00:35:00,869
And I came to mind.

437
00:35:00,953 --> 00:35:04,039
So what could I do?
I couldn't just ignore a friend.

438
00:35:04,123 --> 00:35:07,710
So I helped him sort out the accident.

439
00:35:07,793 --> 00:35:11,588
And before I knew it,
it had gotten this late.

440
00:35:12,589 --> 00:35:13,882
I see.

441
00:35:14,550 --> 00:35:17,469
So your friend just happened to be here.

442
00:35:18,512 --> 00:35:20,681
- And he got into an accident.
- Yeah.

443
00:35:20,764 --> 00:35:23,392
Well, I guess you had no choice.

444
00:35:23,475 --> 00:35:27,020
- Right? You understand, right?
- Yeah, of course.

445
00:35:27,104 --> 00:35:30,899
But I didn't know you had army buddies.

446
00:35:30,983 --> 00:35:34,945
I mean, I didn't see a single one
of your friends at our wedding.

447
00:35:35,028 --> 00:35:36,697
So I thought you had none.

448
00:35:36,780 --> 00:35:41,076
Of course I have friends.
He was just too busy back then.

449
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:42,995
He called me.
He said sorry he couldn't come.

450
00:35:43,078 --> 00:35:44,705
Uh-huh.

451
00:35:44,788 --> 00:35:48,542
But remember when I asked you before?

452
00:35:48,625 --> 00:35:51,754
You told me you were exempt
from military service.

453
00:35:54,923 --> 00:35:56,216
- I did?
- Yes.

454
00:36:05,225 --> 00:36:06,518
What's with you?

455
00:36:07,853 --> 00:36:11,940
You keep leaving the shop,
you forget to pick up Ji-woo.

456
00:36:12,024 --> 00:36:14,359
It's like your mind is somewhere else.

457
00:36:14,443 --> 00:36:18,238
Even today.
Lying to me about what you were up to.

458
00:36:18,322 --> 00:36:19,323
What are you hiding from me?

459
00:36:27,122 --> 00:36:28,874
- Are you seeing someone else?
- No.

460
00:36:28,957 --> 00:36:32,711
Then what is it? Tell me.
Stop lying and just be honest.

461
00:36:32,795 --> 00:36:35,506
It's not like that.
I'm not doing anything wrong.

462
00:36:35,589 --> 00:36:37,716
It's always the same with you.

463
00:36:39,968 --> 00:36:41,929
If you want to live like that,
just get out.

464
00:36:42,054 --> 00:36:44,556
Yeah. You should just get out.

465
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:47,267
Let's take some time apart.

466
00:36:49,436 --> 00:36:50,479
What did you say?

467
00:36:51,313 --> 00:36:52,314
So, what...

468
00:36:52,940 --> 00:36:54,775
Are you saying I should move out?

469
00:36:54,858 --> 00:36:57,027
What about the shop?
And what about Ji-woo?

470
00:36:57,110 --> 00:37:00,697
The shop will be fine without you,
and I can take care of Ji-woo.

471
00:37:04,326 --> 00:37:05,369
It's your choice.

472
00:37:05,452 --> 00:37:07,621
Either be honest with me...

473
00:37:08,288 --> 00:37:10,541
or get kicked out right now.

474
00:37:23,428 --> 00:37:26,098
- Why are you here so early?
- Gong-bok.

475
00:37:26,181 --> 00:37:29,226
Why were you asking about the CCTV?
Is something up?

476
00:37:29,309 --> 00:37:30,602
Tell me something.

477
00:37:31,353 --> 00:37:34,022
Have you been keeping tabs
on Jeong Ho-myeong?

478
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:38,193
Jeong... Oh, yeah. Jeong Ho-myeong.

479
00:37:38,277 --> 00:37:39,987
Did you notice anything suspicious?

480
00:37:40,070 --> 00:37:43,740
For instance,
did he seem to know who we were?

481
00:37:48,453 --> 00:37:50,497
Not at all.

482
00:37:50,581 --> 00:37:54,418
The guy has never even seen my face.
I told you.

483
00:37:54,543 --> 00:37:58,046
That I would forget everything.
I had completely forgotten about it.

484
00:37:58,130 --> 00:38:00,132
- Right?
- Yeah.

485
00:38:00,799 --> 00:38:02,009
Well, that's a relief.

486
00:38:03,635 --> 00:38:06,013
It's just...

487
00:38:06,763 --> 00:38:07,931
I thought I saw him out there.

488
00:38:10,767 --> 00:38:12,019
Oh, is that right?

489
00:38:13,228 --> 00:38:16,106
Well, he lives in the neighborhood,

490
00:38:16,189 --> 00:38:19,067
so maybe you just bumped into him.

491
00:38:20,903 --> 00:38:22,112
I'm gonna head in.

492
00:38:23,030 --> 00:38:24,031
Okay.

493
00:38:34,458 --> 00:38:35,918
What's gotten into him?

494
00:38:37,252 --> 00:38:38,670
When did he get so smart?

495
00:38:45,177 --> 00:38:46,678
NO CALLER ID

496
00:38:52,017 --> 00:38:55,520
- Yes, sir.
- Right. So how'd it go?

497
00:38:56,063 --> 00:38:57,147
With Prosecutor Gang.

498
00:38:57,814 --> 00:39:00,317
- The meeting went well.
- She say anything?

499
00:39:03,695 --> 00:39:06,490
She said she'd look into your case.

500
00:39:06,615 --> 00:39:09,493
That's it? There was nothing else?

501
00:39:09,576 --> 00:39:10,911
Anything at all?

502
00:39:10,994 --> 00:39:12,162
I'm sorry, boss.

503
00:39:13,914 --> 00:39:17,834
No, it's fine. Rome wasn't built in a day.

504
00:39:18,877 --> 00:39:21,296
What matters is what comes next.

505
00:39:23,507 --> 00:39:26,093
I'm counting on you.

506
00:39:26,176 --> 00:39:28,929
You know what I mean, right?

507
00:39:29,638 --> 00:39:33,225
Yes. I'll do my best, no matter what.

508
00:40:02,379 --> 00:40:04,256
Is something wrong?

509
00:40:04,339 --> 00:40:08,051
You should've told me
if you couldn't make it.

510
00:40:09,344 --> 00:40:12,472
Hey, is everything okay?

511
00:40:13,140 --> 00:40:14,516
So...

512
00:40:14,599 --> 00:40:17,185
I'm still at the cafe
in front of the theater.

513
00:40:17,269 --> 00:40:20,772
Please call me when you get this.
I'll be waiting.

514
00:40:27,237 --> 00:40:30,991
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

515
00:40:34,745 --> 00:40:37,330
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG

516
00:40:50,177 --> 00:40:54,473
Here's the thing about love.
It always comes without warning.

517
00:40:55,807 --> 00:41:00,520
On a day you least expect,
in an ordinary, passing moment...

518
00:41:00,645 --> 00:41:03,815
It quietly sits down right beside you.

519
00:41:04,858 --> 00:41:07,152
And because it always begins like that...

520
00:41:07,235 --> 00:41:11,031
you may even discover a side of yourself
you never knew existed.

521
00:41:12,449 --> 00:41:16,953
Here's our first song.
"Rebirth" by Yoon Jong-shin.

522
00:41:30,675 --> 00:41:32,302
- Good night.
- You too.

523
00:41:32,385 --> 00:41:33,678
See you.

524
00:41:36,139 --> 00:41:37,808
This is no time to fool around.

525
00:41:39,059 --> 00:41:41,895
- Hey, did you know?
- What?

526
00:41:41,978 --> 00:41:43,355
A police precinct moved in nearby.

527
00:41:43,438 --> 00:41:46,858
Lately, the cops on the night shift
have been coming to the store a lot.

528
00:41:46,942 --> 00:41:50,112
Damn, why did those bastards
have to move here?

529
00:41:50,195 --> 00:41:51,404
What do we do?

530
00:41:51,488 --> 00:41:53,406
At this rate,
we might not find our merchandise.

531
00:41:53,532 --> 00:41:56,159
Damn, it's not like I can put up
a sign that says "No Cops."

532
00:41:57,077 --> 00:42:00,872
Just wait. Every cop I see,
I'm just gonna...

533
00:42:00,956 --> 00:42:02,499
Beat them up?

534
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,128
I'm gonna be a total asshole to them.

535
00:42:06,211 --> 00:42:08,463
I'll make them never want
to come near the store.

536
00:42:27,858 --> 00:42:29,276
Aren't you going to ring me up?

537
00:42:38,326 --> 00:42:40,287
Damn it.

538
00:42:41,705 --> 00:42:43,331
Damn it.

539
00:43:02,976 --> 00:43:05,103
Can you check me out?

540
00:43:18,408 --> 00:43:20,660
Excuse me, where is the microwave?

541
00:43:21,286 --> 00:43:22,662
Over there.

542
00:43:24,998 --> 00:43:26,291
Thank you.

543
00:45:18,695 --> 00:45:20,155
That'll be 1,600 won.

544
00:45:36,254 --> 00:45:37,505
One's for you.

545
00:45:40,091 --> 00:45:42,844
It's just a little something
to say thank you.

546
00:45:43,762 --> 00:45:45,096
I'll be here often.

547
00:46:03,531 --> 00:46:05,408
How am I supposed to take this?

548
00:46:44,948 --> 00:46:46,032
I got kicked out.

549
00:46:46,950 --> 00:46:48,034
Why?

550
00:46:52,956 --> 00:46:56,251
I've been watching
the scene of Gang's accident.

551
00:46:56,334 --> 00:46:58,545
The Yeongseon River's current
is very strong.

552
00:46:58,628 --> 00:47:02,549
It'll take a while to pull the car out
and to recover the body.

553
00:47:02,632 --> 00:47:03,675
Think she's dead?

554
00:47:03,758 --> 00:47:04,759
No clue.

555
00:47:04,843 --> 00:47:07,178
We'll just have to keep searching
and hope for the best.

556
00:47:13,017 --> 00:47:14,269
Are you okay?

557
00:47:15,395 --> 00:47:16,813
I'm fine, man.

558
00:47:16,896 --> 00:47:18,440
This is nothing.

559
00:47:19,065 --> 00:47:21,526
Take it easy.
You're not getting any younger.

560
00:47:21,609 --> 00:47:23,695
And maybe tone down
the street vendor disguise.

561
00:47:24,279 --> 00:47:25,280
Hey.

562
00:47:26,197 --> 00:47:28,741
It's not like I can just sit
in an office in a suit.

563
00:47:28,825 --> 00:47:30,118
Intel doesn't find itself.

564
00:47:30,201 --> 00:47:33,496
Besides, what's wrong with this?
I gather intel and make a living.

565
00:47:33,580 --> 00:47:35,081
It's the best.

566
00:47:35,165 --> 00:47:36,875
Nothing beats it.

567
00:47:37,625 --> 00:47:39,335
You really never change.

568
00:47:39,752 --> 00:47:40,837
Don't you ever get tired?

569
00:47:41,588 --> 00:47:42,589
What, are you tired?

570
00:47:49,387 --> 00:47:50,972
I've been in Yeongseon for a while.

571
00:47:51,681 --> 00:47:53,516
It's been ten years already.

572
00:47:55,518 --> 00:47:56,686
Time flies, doesn't it?

573
00:48:01,149 --> 00:48:05,487
When I first came here ten years ago?

574
00:48:05,570 --> 00:48:06,571
I thought...

575
00:48:07,155 --> 00:48:08,990
I'd be done with the operation in no time.

576
00:48:12,660 --> 00:48:14,162
But that damn Bulgae.

577
00:48:14,245 --> 00:48:17,624
I searched and searched,
but there was no sign of him.

578
00:48:17,707 --> 00:48:19,751
And the receiver was dead silent.

579
00:48:22,128 --> 00:48:25,965
He has a strange accent,
and he's just a bit shorter than me.

580
00:48:26,049 --> 00:48:27,217
His face...

581
00:48:27,300 --> 00:48:29,636
Do you know
how many tourists like that we get?

582
00:48:29,719 --> 00:48:30,929
Seriously.

583
00:48:33,181 --> 00:48:34,933
May I take a look inside?

584
00:48:35,058 --> 00:48:37,852
Mind your own business.
Get out or I'll call the police.

585
00:48:52,116 --> 00:48:53,451
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

586
00:48:54,911 --> 00:48:56,329
DELIVERY RIDER WANTED

587
00:48:56,412 --> 00:48:57,455
- Delivery!
- Hey.

588
00:48:57,539 --> 00:48:58,623
- Hi.
- The room at the end.

589
00:48:58,706 --> 00:48:59,791
Okay.

590
00:49:06,506 --> 00:49:07,674
Delivery!

591
00:49:10,510 --> 00:49:12,762
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

592
00:49:13,888 --> 00:49:15,181
The whole idea...

593
00:49:16,182 --> 00:49:18,768
...was that I could investigate
more freely...

594
00:49:18,851 --> 00:49:20,103
...as a delivery guy.

595
00:49:25,733 --> 00:49:30,280
You're not quite what we're looking for.

596
00:49:31,281 --> 00:49:33,408
I'm afraid we can't hire you.

597
00:49:47,505 --> 00:49:48,506
Who is that?

598
00:49:48,590 --> 00:49:50,758
He's here for the interview, but he's...

599
00:49:50,842 --> 00:49:52,677
- Well, he's a little on the older side.
- Hired!

600
00:49:54,679 --> 00:49:57,515
- But...
- He's hired.

601
00:49:57,599 --> 00:49:58,891
You're hired.

602
00:50:02,228 --> 00:50:03,563
I'm back.

603
00:50:03,646 --> 00:50:05,315
- Oh, well done.
- You must be freezing.

604
00:50:05,398 --> 00:50:06,733
Not really.

605
00:50:06,816 --> 00:50:10,612
- Here you go. Enjoy your meal.
- Oh my, were you cold?

606
00:50:11,070 --> 00:50:13,072
No, not really.

607
00:50:13,948 --> 00:50:16,909
Hey, stop what you're doing
and make the deliveries.

608
00:50:16,993 --> 00:50:18,411
We agreed I wouldn't.

609
00:50:18,494 --> 00:50:21,789
You're starting today.
And Ho-myeong, you can wait tables.

610
00:50:21,873 --> 00:50:24,083
- No, I'm fine.
- I can't have you catching a cold.

611
00:50:24,751 --> 00:50:26,210
But I have a cold too.

612
00:50:30,590 --> 00:50:31,966
Be safe out there.

613
00:50:34,510 --> 00:50:36,846
But the operation...

614
00:50:37,513 --> 00:50:40,016
...kept taking turns I didn't expect.

615
00:51:03,247 --> 00:51:05,667
This is tough, isn't it? Let me help.

616
00:51:05,750 --> 00:51:07,835
I was hired to be a delivery driver,
wasn't I?

617
00:51:08,586 --> 00:51:12,090
- Why do you have me doing work inside?
- Oh, about that.

618
00:51:15,718 --> 00:51:18,805
It's because you're so good at your job.

619
00:51:18,888 --> 00:51:20,264
You've been promoted.

620
00:51:20,348 --> 00:51:21,391
Promoted.

621
00:51:22,016 --> 00:51:23,685
- Promoted?
- Yes.

622
00:51:25,144 --> 00:51:26,688
Promoted.

623
00:51:31,192 --> 00:51:32,694
- Are you crying?
- No, it's...

624
00:51:33,319 --> 00:51:36,239
It's the onions.
Ugh, my eyes are stinging.

625
00:51:36,364 --> 00:51:39,492
No, don't rub them with your hands.
Hold still. Let me...

626
00:51:40,284 --> 00:51:42,662
Hold on. Oh, goodness.

627
00:51:52,380 --> 00:51:53,798
Ho-myeong.

628
00:51:53,881 --> 00:51:56,718
Your eyes are beautiful.

629
00:52:01,347 --> 00:52:02,932
I guess I should peel some more onions.

630
00:52:03,015 --> 00:52:04,600
These onions, huh?

631
00:52:08,062 --> 00:52:11,482
Ah, wait. I can't.
This isn't right. Hold on.

632
00:52:11,566 --> 00:52:13,943
No, we can't do this.

633
00:52:14,944 --> 00:52:17,864
Life, operations...

634
00:52:19,282 --> 00:52:21,826
You never know what'll happen next.

635
00:52:24,662 --> 00:52:27,123
Who would've thought
ten years would fly by?

636
00:52:27,206 --> 00:52:30,793
That's why I told you not to get married,
but you went and did it anyway.

637
00:52:30,877 --> 00:52:34,255
- You regret it now?
- Who says I regret it?

638
00:52:34,338 --> 00:52:37,884
I have never once regretted
marrying O-ran.

639
00:52:37,967 --> 00:52:39,719
Then what's the problem?

640
00:52:41,387 --> 00:52:42,680
It's just...

641
00:52:46,976 --> 00:52:48,269
I've been a little...

642
00:52:49,562 --> 00:52:50,563
worried.

643
00:52:54,734 --> 00:52:56,360
About what?

644
00:52:59,238 --> 00:53:03,618
I'm worried that the next ten years
might just fly by in a flash too.

645
00:53:05,036 --> 00:53:08,998
What with menopause and all that,
she's getting weaker by the day.

646
00:53:09,957 --> 00:53:14,629
Ji-woo is still just in kindergarten.
Our income isn't stable.

647
00:53:14,712 --> 00:53:17,298
When I first had a family,
I was just so happy.

648
00:53:17,381 --> 00:53:19,091
I felt like I could do anything.

649
00:53:19,175 --> 00:53:22,178
But these days,
seeing how fast time is going by...

650
00:53:24,222 --> 00:53:25,515
It's terrifying.

651
00:53:27,767 --> 00:53:33,439
I wonder if I'll be able to
take care of my family properly.

652
00:53:36,108 --> 00:53:37,401
I'm losing my confidence.

653
00:53:41,239 --> 00:53:44,033
Watching you mope like this,
I know exactly what's wrong.

654
00:53:48,246 --> 00:53:49,914
It's because you're getting old.

655
00:53:51,165 --> 00:53:53,251
Hey, who isn't anxious
about the future at our age?

656
00:53:54,210 --> 00:53:56,212
- You feel that way too?
- Of course.

657
00:53:56,963 --> 00:53:58,631
I'm no exception.

658
00:53:58,714 --> 00:54:01,259
You just live with it.

659
00:54:03,010 --> 00:54:06,055
Just think that you've only lived
half your life.

660
00:54:07,056 --> 00:54:10,101
And just keep dealing with
what's in front of you.

661
00:54:10,935 --> 00:54:11,936
You'll get through it.

662
00:54:13,729 --> 00:54:15,189
And another thing.

663
00:54:15,815 --> 00:54:19,110
Don't try to shoulder the burden yourself.

664
00:54:19,610 --> 00:54:21,404
This operation isn't going well.

665
00:54:21,487 --> 00:54:24,490
And with what happened to O-ran,
you're struggling mentally, too.

666
00:54:24,574 --> 00:54:28,661
That's why as we get older,
we have to rely on each other

667
00:54:28,744 --> 00:54:30,788
to get through life together.

668
00:54:31,789 --> 00:54:33,708
Honestly, have you learned nothing?

669
00:54:41,757 --> 00:54:43,384
Which brings me to my point.

670
00:54:44,385 --> 00:54:46,679
Why don't we stop
doing this operation as a duo?

671
00:54:48,306 --> 00:54:51,017
What do you say we recruit a new member?

672
00:54:52,476 --> 00:54:53,603
Who?

673
00:54:53,686 --> 00:54:55,813
Do you still have contacts at the agency?

674
00:54:55,897 --> 00:54:59,191
No, why look so far?
He's right under our noses.

675
00:55:03,362 --> 00:55:06,741
He wants to take down
Han Gyeong-wook and Yoo In-gu.

676
00:55:07,241 --> 00:55:08,701
He wants it just as badly as we do.

677
00:55:09,827 --> 00:55:12,246
Your rival from ten years ago.

678
00:55:12,371 --> 00:55:15,583
Someone who can take a hell of a beating.

679
00:55:17,376 --> 00:55:19,712
What about Gang Beom-ryong?

680
00:55:22,048 --> 00:55:25,801
- That's ridiculous. Are you drunk?
- I'm not drunk, man.

681
00:55:26,385 --> 00:55:29,263
What I said went in one ear
and out the other, huh?

682
00:55:29,388 --> 00:55:30,806
Listen, man.

683
00:55:30,890 --> 00:55:33,184
I'm a National Intelligence Service agent,
for God's sake.

684
00:55:33,267 --> 00:55:35,269
How can I team up with a thug?

685
00:55:37,813 --> 00:55:39,106
Hey, Ho-myeong.

686
00:55:40,316 --> 00:55:42,276
Let's just face facts.

687
00:55:42,360 --> 00:55:44,528
You're about to turn 50.

688
00:55:45,488 --> 00:55:46,906
You're getting old.

689
00:55:46,989 --> 00:55:48,491
Remember the other day?

690
00:55:48,574 --> 00:55:50,701
When you went to see
Yoo In-gu by yourself?

691
00:55:50,785 --> 00:55:53,496
Back in the day,
think you would've failed against them?

692
00:55:55,748 --> 00:55:58,250
You can't just charge in alone
like you used to.

693
00:55:58,334 --> 00:56:00,294
It won't work anymore.

694
00:56:00,378 --> 00:56:02,672
Listen, that time...

695
00:56:03,798 --> 00:56:04,840
I mean...

696
00:56:10,554 --> 00:56:12,181
I feel bad enough as it is.

697
00:56:12,890 --> 00:56:14,725
Why'd you have to bring up my age?

698
00:56:57,143 --> 00:57:00,396
- Welcome back, boss!
- Yeah.

699
00:57:00,479 --> 00:57:03,107
- Any word from Detective Kim?
- Still recovering the vehicle.

700
00:57:03,190 --> 00:57:06,152
Once the body's found,
it'll be ruled an accidental death.

701
00:57:06,235 --> 00:57:09,113
That damn Detective Kim is so slow.

702
00:57:09,905 --> 00:57:11,490
- Kang-sik.
- Yes, sir.

703
00:57:11,574 --> 00:57:15,453
You need to see that bloated corpse
with your own two eyes.

704
00:57:15,536 --> 00:57:16,787
Understood.

705
00:57:16,871 --> 00:57:18,205
Kang-sik, we're almost there.

706
00:57:18,998 --> 00:57:21,584
Find Martial Arts Master,
and it's smooth sailing.

707
00:57:21,667 --> 00:57:22,960
Wait, boss.

708
00:57:23,044 --> 00:57:26,255
About that Martial Arts Master.
I can't find him anywhere.

709
00:57:27,256 --> 00:57:29,884
I can only track his phone to cell towers,
so it's not helping.

710
00:57:29,967 --> 00:57:33,137
- So you're giving up?
- No, I have to find him. It's just...

711
00:57:33,763 --> 00:57:37,933
We should prepare for the possibility
we don't find him in time.

712
00:57:40,895 --> 00:57:44,148
- See? Now you're using your brain.
- Huh?

713
00:57:44,732 --> 00:57:47,026
You're right. We need a backup plan.

714
00:57:47,109 --> 00:57:49,987
Double our men on the day of the deal.

715
00:57:50,071 --> 00:57:52,948
There's strength in numbers.
What's he going to do when we swarm him?

716
00:57:53,032 --> 00:57:56,077
But a large group will tip off Chief Han.

717
00:57:56,160 --> 00:57:59,163
- That's why you said to keep it small.
- Then we'll just use new faces.

718
00:57:59,246 --> 00:58:02,625
- New faces?
- There's up-and-comers in Yeongseon.

719
00:58:02,750 --> 00:58:06,087
You must know some.
Get them ready for the job.

720
00:58:06,170 --> 00:58:10,466
Our own guys got their asses kicked.
What good will they be?

721
00:58:11,634 --> 00:58:15,054
They can serve as kindling
for the Ingu Sect's fire, can't they?

722
00:58:28,109 --> 00:58:31,987
It must be hard to get things done
when it's freezing out.

723
00:58:33,155 --> 00:58:34,448
Thank you.

724
00:58:35,741 --> 00:58:38,452
But it looks like
there hasn't been much progress.

725
00:58:38,536 --> 00:58:41,664
- Right?
- Progress? Are you kidding?

726
00:58:41,747 --> 00:58:45,459
- It's a fool's errand.
- A fool's errand? Why's that?

727
00:58:46,252 --> 00:58:49,213
The current in the Yeongseon River
is really strong.

728
00:58:49,296 --> 00:58:51,674
Anyone who falls in gets swept away.

729
00:58:51,757 --> 00:58:53,551
They don't just stay there.

730
00:58:54,552 --> 00:58:58,055
They didn't find a body in the car.

731
00:58:58,139 --> 00:59:01,934
Probably got washed up
somewhere around Nakwon Beach.

732
00:59:02,017 --> 00:59:04,353
- Nakwon Beach?
- I'm telling you.

733
00:59:04,436 --> 00:59:08,399
If she washed up over there,
she might've even survived.

734
00:59:08,482 --> 00:59:11,610
I've seen people fall from here
and walk away without a scratch.

735
00:59:12,778 --> 00:59:15,573
But they won't listen to me
no matter what I say.

736
00:59:17,408 --> 00:59:20,286
That's how public officials are.
So frustrating.

737
00:59:24,707 --> 00:59:26,834
Keep pulling!

738
00:59:29,753 --> 00:59:31,422
Nakwon Beach.

739
01:00:07,208 --> 01:00:08,209
Jesus Christ!

740
01:00:08,959 --> 01:00:10,586
-You're awake.
-Who are you?

741
01:00:10,669 --> 01:00:12,588
- Wait!
-Who are you?

742
01:00:12,671 --> 01:00:15,549
Wait, it's me, prosecutor lady.

743
01:00:15,633 --> 01:00:18,052
- How do you know my job?
- You don't remember?

744
01:00:19,053 --> 01:00:21,847
- It's me.
- Who are you?

745
01:00:21,931 --> 01:00:24,099
I'm the one who saved you
on the beach yesterday.

746
01:00:25,309 --> 01:00:27,770
- I carried you here on my back.
- Yesterday?

747
01:00:28,479 --> 01:00:30,898
Are you okay? Can you hear me?

748
01:00:30,981 --> 01:00:31,982
Hey.

749
01:00:36,362 --> 01:00:39,406
Wait, you shouldn't get up yet.
Just a moment.

750
01:00:39,490 --> 01:00:40,491
There we go.

751
01:00:40,866 --> 01:00:42,034
Hold on.

752
01:00:45,913 --> 01:00:49,667
Just a moment.
Let me check your temperature. Hold on.

753
01:00:50,459 --> 01:00:51,961
You're at 37.8 degrees.
It's gone down a bit.

754
01:00:52,044 --> 01:00:53,379
Just a moment.

755
01:00:53,462 --> 01:00:57,758
Since you fell into the sea yesterday,
you need to keep warm.

756
01:00:59,635 --> 01:01:01,136
Hold on.

757
01:01:01,220 --> 01:01:04,306
Okay. There you go.

758
01:01:05,599 --> 01:01:09,019
You might feel fine,
but your fever could suddenly spike.

759
01:01:09,103 --> 01:01:10,312
But, wait.

760
01:01:10,980 --> 01:01:13,649
- Hold on, let me get you some water.
- No. Wait a minute.

761
01:01:13,732 --> 01:01:17,820
- Yes?
- I remember you saving me.

762
01:01:17,903 --> 01:01:19,488
But where am I?

763
01:01:19,613 --> 01:01:22,116
- This doesn't seem like a hospital.
- Oh, here?

764
01:01:23,450 --> 01:01:24,535
A temporary...

765
01:01:26,120 --> 01:01:29,248
- ...shelter.
- Shelter?

766
01:01:29,331 --> 01:01:32,459
Man, that Martial Arts Master
or whatever must be pretty scary.

767
01:01:32,543 --> 01:01:35,212
But don't you think you're overdoing it?

768
01:01:36,880 --> 01:01:40,342
He had a crazed look in his eyes.
I think he'll cause trouble again.

769
01:01:41,844 --> 01:01:45,139
The prosecutor was taken care of, right?

770
01:01:45,264 --> 01:01:48,726
Yes, once we recover the body,
it'll be ruled as an accidental death.

771
01:01:58,027 --> 01:01:59,695
If it weren't for this.

772
01:01:59,778 --> 01:02:02,990
It even has In-gu's voice on it.

773
01:02:03,073 --> 01:02:04,199
It's foolproof.

774
01:02:06,368 --> 01:02:09,330
Okay, good job. Good work.

775
01:02:11,332 --> 01:02:12,624
Listen.

776
01:02:13,625 --> 01:02:16,545
If this gets to the police,
I'll be arrested too.

777
01:02:17,713 --> 01:02:19,298
- Mr. Geum.
- Yes?

778
01:02:19,381 --> 01:02:22,551
I want President Yoo
to complete the drug deal safely.

779
01:02:22,634 --> 01:02:25,304
Don't worry, man.
I won't turn this over to the police.

780
01:02:25,387 --> 01:02:27,097
Never, not at all.

781
01:02:27,848 --> 01:02:28,849
Wait.

782
01:02:30,601 --> 01:02:32,436
What do you need this for then?

783
01:02:33,062 --> 01:02:34,938
I'll have to figure that out as we go.

784
01:02:35,939 --> 01:02:37,191
You sure are curious.

785
01:02:38,734 --> 01:02:40,861
Listen, Mr. Geum.
You just focus on one thing.

786
01:02:40,944 --> 01:02:43,405
Rebuilding the Ingu Sect
to be the Kang-sik Sect.

787
01:02:43,489 --> 01:02:44,948
Let's get the ball rolling. Okay?

788
01:02:46,075 --> 01:02:48,869
Yes. I'll make the preparations.

789
01:02:49,244 --> 01:02:51,413
- Okay.
- Oh, one more thing.

790
01:02:56,585 --> 01:03:00,214
Mr. Geum is one ambitious man.

791
01:03:00,297 --> 01:03:01,590
All right then.

792
01:03:04,802 --> 01:03:06,678
He'll make it big in no time.

793
01:04:27,885 --> 01:04:32,014
- Wait, that one's not expired yet.
- Oh. Right.

794
01:04:33,265 --> 01:04:35,184
It's not like you to make such a mistake.

795
01:04:36,185 --> 01:04:40,481
Did something happen yesterday
with the CCTV footage?

796
01:04:44,735 --> 01:04:47,237
Yesterday, I met Jeong Ho-myeong.

797
01:04:49,281 --> 01:04:51,909
You met Jeong Ho-myeong?

798
01:04:51,992 --> 01:04:53,076
Right.

799
01:04:54,328 --> 01:04:59,291
But that guy didn't just know me.
He knows a lot about you, too.

800
01:05:01,126 --> 01:05:02,377
Did he?

801
01:05:02,961 --> 01:05:06,173
- He said he knew me?
- Yeah.

802
01:05:06,256 --> 01:05:09,051
And not just our faces.

803
01:05:10,260 --> 01:05:12,888
He even knows why we came
to Yeongseon Island ten years ago.

804
01:05:13,972 --> 01:05:15,891
He knew about us, inside and out.

805
01:05:21,104 --> 01:05:22,231
Okay, look.

806
01:05:23,106 --> 01:05:24,942
- There's something I need to tell you.
- Go on.

807
01:05:44,962 --> 01:05:47,756
SPECIAL THANKS TO KWON YUL

808
01:06:02,437 --> 01:06:06,400
Listen up, I'm about to make you
an offer you can't refuse.

809
01:06:06,525 --> 01:06:09,611
You're getting old.
You can't do anything by yourself anymore.

810
01:06:09,695 --> 01:06:11,196
I accept your offer.

811
01:06:11,280 --> 01:06:12,614
-Move.
-Out of my way!

812
01:06:12,698 --> 01:06:14,908
That bastard Yoo In-gu is dealing drugs?

813
01:06:14,992 --> 01:06:17,744
- Let's focus on our deal.
- You don't remember anything?

814
01:06:17,828 --> 01:06:20,247
- I have no idea.
- Did you find out who she is?

815
01:06:20,330 --> 01:06:21,790
Mi-kyung is interested in me too.

816
01:06:22,791 --> 01:06:23,792
Should I just lock him up?

817
01:06:25,252 --> 01:06:27,588
- She'll probably just tear it.
- We don't work for you.

818
01:06:27,671 --> 01:06:29,715
- It's over.
- We face them head-on.

819
01:06:29,798 --> 01:06:33,010
- Are you sure you can take them down?
- I'll find a way.

